The key bindings on VIM:

direction -> hjkl as in vim.

NORMAL MODE: Moving about window panes: Ctrl + direction
Save: ,w (insert and normal).
Save + quit: ,r (insert and normal).

Completion:
<C-x><C-n> : keyword local completion. (forward, <C-p> is backward)
<C-x><C-l> : line local completion.
<C-x><C-f> : file name completion.

Vim Surround:
cs<old><new> : changes the surrounding parens or XML-like tag.
ds<surr> : removes the surrounding the cursor.
ys<motion/block><surr> : surrounds the motion or block with surr.
Visual mode: S<surr> : surround S with surr.

TComment:
gc<motion> : toggles commenting for <motion> observing file type.
gcc : toggles commenting for the line.
Visual: gc toggles, g> forces comment.
